Fed’s Bullard Says ‘Monetary Policy Cannot Do Everything’

-- B y   S t e v e   M a t t h e w s   a n d   K a t h l e e n   H a y s
-- 
2011-08-26T21:42:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/fed-s-bullard-says-monetary-policy-cannot-do-everything-.html
St. Louis Federal Reserve Bank
President  James Bullard  said the central bank’s role in
supporting growth is limited, and fiscal policy must also work
to aid the economy.  “Monetary policy cannot do everything,” Bullard said
today in a Bloomberg Radio interview in  Jackson Hole ,  Wyoming .
“We can do our part, but that is only one part of the
macroeconomic picture.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
Steve Matthews in Atlanta at 
